SIMPLE: inquisitive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inquisitive
<hw>In*quis"i*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>inquisitif</ets>, F. <ets>inquisitif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Disposed to ask questions, especially in matters which do not
concern the inquirer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A wise man is not <qex>inquisitive</qex> about things
impertinent.</q> <rj><qau>Broome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Given to examination, investigation, or research;
searching; curious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A young, <qex>inquisitive</qex>, and sprightly genius.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Inquiring; prying; curious; meddling;
intrusive.</syn> <usage> -- <er>Inquisitive</er>, <er>Curious</er>,
<er>Prying</er>. <xex>Curious</xex> denotes a feeling, and
<xex>inquisitive</xex> a habit. We are <xex>curious</xex> when we desire
to learn something new; we are <xex>inquisitive</xex> when we set
ourselves to gain it by inquiry or research. <xex>Prying</xex> implies
<xex>inquisitiveness</xex>, and is more commonly used in a bad sense, as
indicating a desire to penetrate into the secrets of others.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[We] <qex>curious</qex> are to hear,⟦br⟧
What happens new.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This folio of four pages [a newspaper], happy work!⟦br⟧
Which not even critics criticise; that holds⟦br⟧
<qex>Inquisitive</qex> attention, while I read.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor need we with a <qex>prying</qex> eye survey⟦br⟧
The distant skies, to find the Milky Way.</q>
<rj><qau>Creech.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inquisitive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inquisitive
<hw>In*quis"i*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who is inquisitive;
one curious in research.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Temple.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inquisitively</ent>⟦br⟧
